## Example 3 — Compare Distributions

Compare exam score distributions for two Algebra 2 classes using the mean and standard deviation.

Results:

* Mr. Jackson’s class:
  * mean `= 93.2`
  * standard deviation `= 2.3`
* Ms. Hettrick’s class:
  * mean `= 79.9`
  * standard deviation `= 7.2`

Interpretation:

* Mr. Jackson’s class scored higher on average
* Ms. Hettrick’s class scores are more spread out

